### Authentication Server Tests

### 1. Register a new user
POST http://localhost:8081/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User"
}

> {% client.global.set("username", "testuser"); client.global.set("password", "password123"); %}

### 2. Login to get JWT
POST http://localhost:8081/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

> {% client.global.set("access_token", response.body.access_token); client.global.set("refresh_token", response.body.refresh_token); %}

### Resource Service Tests

### 3. Access public resource (requires authentication)
GET http://localhost:8082/api/resource/public
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### 4. Access user resource (requires role 'user' or 'admin')
GET http://localhost:8082/api/resource/user
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### 5. Access admin resource (requires role 'admin')
GET http://localhost:8082/api/resource/admin
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}
